9. 
<taxonomicName authority="R. Grether" authorityName="R. Grether" box="[164,496,1420,1447]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="candollei">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[164,370,1420,1447]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Mimosa candollei</emphasis>
R. Grether
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1420,1591]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
Considered as 
<emphasis box="[307,487,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">M. quadrivalvis</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[497,669,1456,1483]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" rank="variety" variety="leptocarpa">
var. 
<emphasis box="[548,669,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">leptocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barneby, R. C." box="[717,900,1457,1483]" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 835" part="65" refString="Barneby, R. C. (1991) Sensitivae Censitae: a description of the genus Mimosa L. (Mimosaceae) in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 65: 1 - 835." title="Sensitivae Censitae: a description of the genus Mimosa L. (Mimosaceae) in the New World" type="journal article" year="1991">Barneby (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, but segregated as a distinct species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grether, R." journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="29 - 37" part="10" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307/3393180" refString="Grether, R. (2000) Nomenclatural changes in the genus Mimosa (Fabaceae, Mimosoideae) in southern Mexico and Central America. Novon 10: 29 - 37. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 3393180" title="Nomenclatural changes in the genus Mimosa (Fabaceae, Mimosoideae) in southern Mexico and Central America" type="journal article" year="2000">Grether (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. None of the other infraspecific taxa assigned to 
<emphasis box="[763,940,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">M. quadrivalvis</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barneby, R. C." box="[982,1159,1493,1519]" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 835" part="65" refString="Barneby, R. C. (1991) Sensitivae Censitae: a description of the genus Mimosa L. (Mimosaceae) in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 65: 1 - 835." title="Sensitivae Censitae: a description of the genus Mimosa L. (Mimosaceae) in the New World" type="journal article" year="1991">Barneby (1991)</bibRefCitation>
occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[1265,1351,1493,1519]" name="Bolivia" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<taxonomicName box="[1361,1451,1493,1518]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">Mimosa</taxonomicName>
candollei
</emphasis>
is a widespread and weedy ruderal along roadsides and in abandoned pastures across much of seasonally dry South America.
</paragraph>
